headline: Why AbbVie (ABBV) Shares Are Falling Today
summary: Shares of pharmaceutical company AbbVie (NYSE:ABBV) fell 3.9% in the afternoon session after the company reported third-quarter results that were overshadowed by a steep drop in profitability and a reduced earnings forecast for the full year. Although AbbVie's quarterly revenue of $15.78 billion and adjusted earnings per share (EPS) of $1.86 both surpassed Wall Street's estimates, investors focused on underlying weaknesses. headline: Monster (MNST): Buy, Sell, or Hold Post Q2 Earnings?
summary: Even though Monster (currently trading at $65.28 per share) has gained 8.6% over the last six months, it has lagged the S&P 500’s 22.6% return during that period. This might have investors contemplating their next move.
